AT ME FOR SOME REASON?

233
00:10:22,237 --> 00:10:24,171
<i>Ari.</i>

234
00:10:24,206 --> 00:10:25,973
<i>- ARE YOU?
- Ari.</i>

235
00:10:26,008 --> 00:10:28,743
- WOULD YOU DO THAT?
- NO, I WOULDN'T.

236
00:10:28,777 --> 00:10:30,578
HOW WOULD I KNOW
IF YOU'RE LYING TO ME?

237
00:10:30,612 --> 00:10:32,380
<i>You wouldn't.
But I'm not.</i>

238
00:10:32,414 --> 00:10:35,650
- WHERE ARE YOU?
- I'M NOT WHEREVER YOU ARE,
SO RELAX.

239
00:10:35,684 --> 00:10:38,719
EDDIE, I HAVE GIVEN YOU TONS
OF BUSINESS OVER THE YEARS.

240
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,421
I WANT ONE ANSWER.

241
00:10:40,455 --> 00:10:43,558
HAS TERRANCE McQUIEWICK
HIRED YOU TO LOOK AT ME?

242
00:10:43,592 --> 00:10:45,593
NO, ARI.
TERRANCE HASN'T HIRED
ME TO DO ANYTHING.

243
00:10:45,627 --> 00:10:48,896
BUT THAT'S ALL
I CAN TELL YOU, ALL RIGHT?
I'M SORRY.

244
00:10:50,899 --> 00:10:53,467
- I THINK YOU'RE OVERREACTING.
- OH, YOU DO?

245
00:10:53,502 --> 00:10:56,070
IT WAS A HARMLESS
LITTLE CLICK OF THE MOUSE.

246
00:10:56,071 --> 00:10:58,606
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY PEOPLE
REQUEST TO BE MY FRIEND?

247
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:01,642
<i>- I DON'T ACCEPT THEM ALL.
- I DIDN'T WANT TO BE RUDE.</i>

248
00:11:01,677 --> 00:11:04,912
THIS IS REALLY
CONVENIENT TIMING THOUGH,
WOULDN'T YOU SAY?

249
00:11:04,947 --> 00:11:07,381
NO, IT'S TERRIBLE TIMING,
'CAUSE NOW YOU'RE GONNA
LEAVE ALL UPSET.

250
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:09,650
SORRY FOR YOUR GUILT.

251
00:11:09,685 --> 00:11:11,819
JAMIE, PLEASE.
THIS IS HARD ENOUGH
ALREADY.

252
00:11:11,854 --> 00:11:13,754
CAN YOU PLEASE JUST TRUST ME
AND FORGET ABOUT IT?

253
00:11:13,789 --> 00:11:16,190
I KNOW I'M FORGETTING
SOMETHING.

254
00:11:16,225 --> 00:11:19,026
YOU HAVE EVERYTHING.
I LOOKED UNDER THE BED,
I OPENED EVERY DRAWER.

255
00:11:19,061 --> 00:11:21,128
<i>I JUST WANT TO MAKE SURE
YOU AND I ARE OKAY.</i>

256
00:11:21,129 --> 00:11:23,664
- THEN DELETE HER.
- DELETE HER?

257
00:11:23,699 --> 00:11:26,267
YEAH, TAKE HER OFF
YOUR FRIENDS LIST.

258
00:11:30,672 --> 00:11:33,507
DONE.
FEEL BETTER?

259
00:11:33,542 --> 00:11:35,009
NOT REALLY.

260
00:11:35,043 --> 00:11:37,411
- JAMIE, COME ON.
- DO YOU WANT ME TO GO?

261
00:11:37,446 --> 00:11:38,946
<i>NO, I DON'T WANT YOU TO GO.</i>

262
00:11:38,981 --> 00:11:41,382
BUT THIS IS GONNA BE
A GREAT OPPORTUNITY.

263
00:11:41,416 --> 00:11:43,484
IT'S GONNA BE
AMAZING FOR YOU.

264
00:11:46,788 --> 00:11:48,389
I'M REALLY GONNA MISS YOU.

265
00:11:48,423 --> 00:11:50,725
BABY, NO.
DON'T CRY.

266
00:11:50,759 --> 00:11:53,494
I'LL BE WAITING RIGHT HERE
FOR YOU WHEN YOU GET BACK.

267
00:11:58,734 --> 00:12:00,568
<i>Lloyd:
Johnny, you're making
yourself crazy.</i>

268
00:12:00,602 --> 00:12:02,837
NO, THEY'RE MAKING ME CRAZY.
THIS WAS A SETUP.

269
00:12:02,871 --> 00:12:05,306
- NO, IT WASN'T.
- WHY DIDN'T YOU KNOW
ABOUT THIS?

270
00:12:05,307 --> 00:12:08,676
WHY DIDN'T YOU PREPARE ME?
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME I HAD
A CONFLICT WITH THE DIRECTOR?

271
00:12:08,710 --> 00:12:11,012
I CAN'T KEEP TRACK OF ALL
YOUR CONFLICTS, JOHNNY.

272
00:12:11,046 --> 00:12:14,048
<i>- THIS GUY'S AN ANIMAL.
- Charm him with your
winning smile.</i>

273
00:12:14,082 --> 00:12:16,417
MR. CHASE,
THEY'RE READY FOR YOU.

274
00:12:16,451 --> 00:12:18,286
GREAT, THEY'RE READY.

275
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,354
JOHNNY DRAMA,
THIS IS YOUR MOMENT.

276
00:12:20,355 --> 00:12:24,759
NOW STEP UP AND SHINE BRIGHT
FOR ALL THE WORLD TO SEE.

277
00:12:24,793 --> 00:12:26,194
I GOT TO GO.

278
00:12:26,228 --> 00:12:27,828
BREAK A LEG.

279
00:12:27,863 --> 00:12:31,299
- JOHNNY CHASE, EVERYONE.
- OKAY.

280
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,935
- HEY, EVERYONE.
- SORRY TO KEEP YOU
WAITING, JOHNNY.

281
00:12:33,969 --> 00:12:36,337
<i>- TECHNICAL PROBLEMS
WITH THE CAMERA.
- THAT'S OKAY.</i>

282
00:12:36,371 --> 00:12:38,472
JUST AS LONG AS YOU
WEREN'T FREEZING ME OUT

283
00:12:38,507 --> 00:12:40,208
'CAUSE THIS GUY IS
STILL MAD AT ME.

284
00:12:40,242 --> 00:12:41,642
WHY WOULD HE BE
MAD AT YOU?

285
00:12:41,677 --> 00:12:43,678
LAST TIME JOHN AUDITIONED
FOR ME ONE OF MY COLLEAGUES

286
00:12:43,712 --> 00:12:45,580
KEPT CHECKING HIS EMAIL.
JOHN GOT A LITTLE UPSET.

287
00:12:45,614 --> 00:12:48,816
YEAH, BUT IT'S OKAY NOW.
YOU CAN TALK IN THE MIDDLE
OF MY AUDITION.

288
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:51,786
YOU CAN SCREAM AND YELL--
WHATEVER. NOTHING FAZES
ME ANYMORE.

289
00:12:51,820 --> 00:12:54,222
THAT'S GOOD, JOHNNY,
'CAUSE WE DON'T WANT
TO TRY AND FAZE YOU.

290
00:12:54,256 --> 00:12:56,891
JUST RELAX.
EVERYBODY HERE IS HOPING
THAT YOU'RE THE GUY.

291
00:12:56,925 --> 00:12:59,493
IN FACT, I'M GONNA TURN
THIS OFF RIGHT NOW

292
00:12:59,528 --> 00:13:01,162
SO THERE'S NOTHING
TO DISTRACT YOU, OKAY?

293
00:13:01,196 --> 00:13:04,498
- THANK YOU.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.
LET'S DO THIS.

294
00:13:09,238 --> 00:13:11,172
( clears throat )

295
00:13:11,206 --> 00:13:12,707
OKAY, LET'S DO IT.

296
00:13:12,741 --> 00:13:15,910
TWO SECONDS.
( exhales )

297
00:13:15,944 --> 00:13:17,345
HERE WE GO.

298
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:19,680
ALL RIGHT, GENTLEMEN.
LET'S DO THIS.  OH!

299
00:13:19,715 --> 00:13:22,817
I'M SORRY.
I GUESS I'M HERE EARLY.
NOBODY WAS--

300
00:13:22,851 --> 00:13:25,520
THAT'S OKAY, DEAN.
WE'RE JUST RUNNING
A LITTLE BEHIND.

301
00:13:25,554 --> 00:13:28,756
<i>- WE'LL BE ABOUT FIVE MINUTES.
- I'LL JUST WAIT OUTSIDE.</i>

302
00:13:28,790 --> 00:13:31,692
- HEY, DRAMA.
- DEAN.

303
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:34,362
<i>GOOD LUCK, MAN.
SORRY.</i>

304
00:13:34,396 --> 00:13:37,164
- OKAY, HERE WE GO.
- HE'S TESTING TOO?

305
00:13:37,199 --> 00:13:40,535
<i>- I THOUGHT IT WAS JUST ME.
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT DEAN, JOHN.</i>

306
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:43,738
- FUCKING SUPERMAN.
- HEY, YOU'RE GONNA DO GREAT.

307
00:13:43,805 --> 00:13:45,373
IT'S YOUR JOB TO LOSE.

308
00:13:49,545 --> 00:13:51,379
OKAY, LET'S DO IT.

309
00:13:51,413 --> 00:13:55,049
GOD, I HAVEN'T AUDITIONED
IN LIKE THREE YEARS.

310
00:13:57,686 --> 00:14:00,154
( breathing heavily )

311
00:14:04,026 --> 00:14:06,460
DO YOU GUYS MIND IF I
JUST STEP OUT FOR A SECOND?

312
00:14:06,495 --> 00:14:08,563
WE'RE KIND OF ON
A TIGHT SCHEDULE.

313
00:14:08,597 --> 00:14:11,265
- I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
- HEY, JOHN.

314
00:14:12,868 --> 00:14:14,569
- THAT'S A MELTDOWN.
- UH-HUH.

315
00:14:14,603 --> 00:14:16,571
COME ON, JOHNNY, YOU'VE GOT
TO GET BACK IN THERE.

316
00:14:16,605 --> 00:14:20,007
BRO, I CAN'T.
I THINK I'M HAVING
A HEART ATTACK.

317
00:14:20,042 --> 00:14:23,678
JUST TAKE A DEEP BREATH.
YOU KNOW YOU'RE ONLY HAVING
A PANIC ATTACK.

318
00:14:23,712 --> 00:14:27,048
I'VE HAD 100 PANIC ATTACKS
IN MY LIFE, THIS ISN'T
A PANIC ATTACK.

319
00:14:27,082 --> 00:14:29,217
<i>- JOHNNY.. - Vince.</i>

320
00:14:29,251 --> 00:14:32,720
<i>- Yes, Johnny?
- I THINK I PEED MYSELF.</i>

321
00:14:32,754 --> 00:14:34,889
UH...

322
00:14:34,923 --> 00:14:37,625
OKAY, JOHNNY,
I'M COMING TO GET YOU.

323
00:14:37,659 --> 00:14:40,828
HURRY, BRO.

324
00:14:40,863 --> 00:14:42,797
I'VE GOT TO GO.

325
00:14:44,132 --> 00:14:45,933
SOMEONE'S RUNNING BEHIND.

326
00:14:45,968 --> 00:14:48,102
- YEAH, I HAD
A DOCTOR'S APPOINTMENT.
- OH, I DIDN'T KNOW.

327
00:14:48,136 --> 00:14:50,171
- IT WAS A LAST MINUTE THING.
- EVERYTHING OKAY?

328
00:14:50,205 --> 00:14:53,040
YEAH YEAH.
BUT IF HE CALLS, JUST PUT
IT RIGHT THROUGH, PLEASE.

329
00:14:53,075 --> 00:14:55,776
SURE.  HERE ARE
YOUR OTHER MESSAGES.
ALSO, MY FRIEND RICKY CALLED.

330
00:14:55,811 --> 00:14:57,745
HATE TO GET INVOLVED, BUT I
THINK SHE KIND OF LIKES YOU.

331
00:14:57,779 --> 00:15:01,082
- OH, COOL.
- SO SHOULD I TELL HER
YOU'LL CALL HER?

332
00:15:01,116 --> 00:15:03,651
YEAH, I'M GONNA BE TAKING
A BREAK FROM THE DATING
POOL FOR A WHILE.

333
00:15:03,685 --> 00:15:06,687
- MURPHY GROUP, HEY.
- WHAT'S UP, SCOTT?

334
00:15:06,722 --> 00:15:09,023
WHAT'S UP, MAMA?
SO I HEARD YOU HAD

335
00:15:09,057 --> 00:15:10,491
A WILD PARTY NIGHT
AT VILLA.

336
00:15:10,526 --> 00:15:12,927
OH YEAH?
HOW'D YOU HEAR THAT?

337
00:15:12,961 --> 00:15:14,996
WELL, THE GIRL THAT YOU WERE
SUCKING FACE WITH, TARA,

338
00:15:15,097 --> 00:15:17,832
I KNOW HER--
WELL, SOME FRIENDS OF MINE
ACTUALLY KNOW HER...

339
00:15:17,866 --> 00:15:20,468
- WELL.
- I DIDN'T HEAR ANYTHING.

340
00:15:22,037 --> 00:15:23,671
- SCOTT.
- YEAH?

341
00:15:25,007 --> 00:15:27,375
WHAT DO YOUR FRIENDS
KNOW ABOUT HER?

342
00:15:27,409 --> 00:15:30,111
UH, SHE'S NOT LIKE YOUR
GIRLFRIEND OR ANYTHING?

343
00:15:30,145 --> 00:15:32,046
SHE'S NOT MY GIRLFRIEND.
I DON'T EVEN KNOW THE GIRL.

344
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:34,215
- WELL, YOU KNOW HER
A LITTLE BIT.
- WHAT DO I KNOW?

345
00:15:34,249 --> 00:15:36,384
- I DON'T KNOW.
THE SAME THING I KNOW.
- WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

346
00:15:36,451 --> 00:15:39,187
THAT SHE KEEPS IT MOVING.
SHE GETS AROUND.

347
00:15:39,221 --> 00:15:41,455
SHE GETS AROUND?
SCOTT, WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?
HAVE YOU BEEN WITH HER?

348
00:15:41,490 --> 00:15:43,491
NO, NOT MY STYLE.

349
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:45,793
- THE GIRL'S LIKE A PETRI DISH.
- WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

350
00:15:45,827 --> 00:15:48,896
I KNOW THAT CLIFF CANTOR
AND RICK SALOMON DOUBLE
TEAMED HER

351
00:15:48,897 --> 00:15:51,899
AT A PARTY A COUPLE
WEEKS AGO, WHICH IS NOT
EXCELLENT FOR YOU.

352
00:15:51,967 --> 00:15:54,135
- JESUS.
- OH HEY, LISTEN.

353
00:15:54,169 --> 00:15:57,138
YOU KNOW WHAT?
IF YOU LIKE HER,
YOU CAN CHANGE HER.

354
00:15:57,172 --> 00:15:59,240
<i>A NICE BOY LIKE YOU CAN
REFORM A GIRL LIKE THAT.</i>

355
00:15:59,308 --> 00:16:01,542
- YOU GOT TO GET
THE DOCTOR ON THE PHONE.
- VINCE JUST CALLED.

356
00:16:01,610 --> 00:16:03,644
- HE'S ON HIS WAY TO
THE HOSPITAL WITH DRAMA.
- WHY?

357
00:16:03,679 --> 00:16:05,479
HE THINKS DRAMA
HAD A HEART ATTACK.

358
00:16:05,514 --> 00:16:07,348
- OH MY GOD.
- THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY
TO CEDARS.

359
00:16:07,382 --> 00:16:10,184
TEXT ME WHERE I'M GOING.

360
00:16:11,453 --> 00:16:13,487
<i> I'VE BEEN UP
AND ON MY FEET </i>

361
00:16:13,522 --> 00:16:15,690
<i> SINCE THE BREAK OF DAY </i>

362
00:16:15,724 --> 00:16:18,526
<i> YOU'VE BEEN DOWN THE ROAD
THERE, BABY... </i>

363
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,461
( barking )

364
00:16:22,030 --> 00:16:25,266
MELINDA.
MY LOVE, HOW ARE YOU?

365
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:28,302
ARI GOLD, LONG TIME.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

366
00:16:28,337 --> 00:16:30,905
I HAVE A MEETING.
TV STUFF, BORING.
FUNNY RUNNING INTO YOU.

367
00:16:30,939 --> 00:16:32,974
- I JUST SAW YOUR HUSBAND.
- REALLY?

368
00:16:33,008 --> 00:16:36,844
YEAH, STILL NOT LOOKING
QUITE ALIVE ENOUGH TO
HAVE GOTTEN YOU.

369
00:16:36,879 --> 00:16:38,746
UH-HUH.  HOW WAS
YOUR LITTLE REUNION?

370
00:16:38,780 --> 00:16:40,715
- THERE'S STILL SOME
BITTERNESS THERE.
- I BET.

371
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:44,151
YEAH.  SO HAS HE SAID
ANYTHING ABOUT THAT LATELY?

372
00:16:44,186 --> 00:16:46,721
- ANYTHING ABOUT WHAT?
- ANYTHING ABOUT OUR
BITTERNESS?

373
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:49,757
UH, NO, ARI.
WE DON'T TALK ABOUT
YOU VERY OFTEN.

374
00:16:49,791 --> 00:16:51,192
OH, COME ON, MELINDA.

375
00:16:51,226 --> 00:16:53,694
YOU USED TO TALK ABOUT
ME VERY OFTEN BEFORE
YOU MET TERRANCE.

376
00:16:53,729 --> 00:16:55,363
- WHAT IS THIS?
- WHAT?

377
00:16:55,397 --> 00:16:57,131
DID YOU COME HERE
FOR A REASON?

378
00:16:57,165 --> 00:16:59,100
- YES I DID.
- THEN SPEAK.

379
00:16:59,134 --> 00:17:02,103
TERRANCE CAME
TO ME THIS MORNING,
AS I'M SURE YOU KNOW,

380
00:17:02,137 --> 00:17:04,672
BECAUSE HE WOULD LIKE
FOR ME TO BUY HIM OUT.

381
00:17:04,706 --> 00:17:06,374
I DIDN'T KNOW.

382
00:17:06,408 --> 00:17:08,709
YEAH, THAT'S GREAT.
BUT I KNOW YOU KNOW.

383
00:17:08,744 --> 00:17:11,345
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING, ARI.

384
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:14,415
MELINDA, COME ON.
WE HAD A MOMENT
OF FLIRTATION.

385
00:17:14,449 --> 00:17:17,451
I'M SORRY IF YOU'RE
BITTER ALSO BECAUSE I
CHOSE MY WIFE OVER YOU.

386
00:17:17,519 --> 00:17:20,888
BUT I REPRESENTED YOUR TALENPRE.

387
00:17:20,923 --> 00:17:22,757
REVISIONIST HISTORY, ARI.

388
00:17:22,791 --> 00:17:25,426
YOU CHOSE YOUR WIFE
OVER ME 'CAUSE YOU
COULDN'T GET ME.

389
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:28,329
AND YOU REPRESENTED ME
OVER HER 'CAUSE I HAD
MORE TALENT.

390
00:17:28,330 --> 00:17:31,799
LINE UP OUR RESUMES,
I THINK MOST WOULD AGREE.

391
00:17:31,867 --> 00:17:35,803
MELINDA, I KNOW HOW MUCH
TERRANCE TRUSTS YOU.

392
00:17:35,837 --> 00:17:38,239
NOW IF YOU GUYS WANT OUT,
I'IN.

393
00:17:38,273 --> 00:17:41,042
BUT I GOT YOU YOUR FIRST JOB,
SO DON'T LET ME BE PLAYED.

394
00:17:41,076 --> 00:17:43,711
HONEY, YOU KNOW
YOU NEVER GET PLAYED.

395
00:17:43,745 --> 00:17:45,846
AND ALL I'LL TELL YOU
IS THIS--

396
00:17:45,881 --> 00:17:47,849
<i>I'M NO LONGER ON THE INSIDE.</i>

397
00:17:47,883 --> 00:17:50,184
LOOK UP A 25-YEAR-OLD
D-CUP NAMED KELSEY.

398
00:17:50,252 --> 00:17:52,687
- MAYBE SHE CAN HELP.
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

399
00:17:52,688 --> 00:17:55,857
I MEAN MY HUSBAND
IS A LYING SCUMBAG

400
00:17:55,891 --> 00:17:58,492
AND I HAD NO IDEA
HE WAS TRYING TO SELL

401
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:00,528
UNTIL RIGHT NOW.

402
00:18:01,797 --> 00:18:04,165
SO YOU HIRED
EDDIE KAPOWSKI?

403
00:18:04,199 --> 00:18:06,834
I'M LATE FOR MY
POLE DANCING CLASS, ARI.

404
00:18:11,406 --> 00:18:13,808
GUESS I'M REALLY GOING.

405
00:18:13,842 --> 00:18:16,110
YEAH.

406
00:18:16,144 --> 00:18:19,347
YOU'RE SO STRONG.
NO TEARS AT ALL.

407
00:18:19,381 --> 00:18:21,782
I'M A GUY.
WE DON'T CRY.

408
00:18:21,817 --> 00:18:24,519
NOT EVEN ON REALLY SAD
OCCASIONS?

409
00:18:24,553 --> 00:18:26,654
I'M CRYING ON THE INSIDE.

410
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:35,596
TURTLE, I'VE BEEN
THINKING A LOT ABOUT

411
00:18:35,631 --> 00:18:39,433
THIS WHOLE SEPARATION
AND THE FACEBOOK THING.

412
00:18:39,468 --> 00:18:41,269
YOU'VE BEEN THINKING
SINCE LUNCH?

413
00:18:41,303 --> 00:18:43,871
